&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a Modern Matron with excellent management skills within an acute care setting looking for a new challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If so then we would love to talk to you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a Matron who is dynamic and compassionate to promote best practice and high quality care for people who use our services and their families. The role will be expected to drive clinical excellence and quality agenda to ensure our services are needs lead and evidence based. It will also oversee the development of our registered and unregistered staff in order improve quality of the care and services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post as &lt;strong&gt;Modern Matron&lt;/strong&gt; within our Older Persons Mental Health Inpatient services based at Parklands Hospital, covering two Wards and ECT department in Basingstoke.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be given opportunities to utilise your skills in direct clinical management of complex service users, ensuring systems are in place to support care, supporting and developing staff groups. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We are looking for someone with a proven track record for managing and leading teams at a senior level, and experience within the acute care field. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; If you would like to discuss this opportunity or arrange a visit to the service, please contact Richard Ilsley, Head of Nursing &amp; Allied Health Professionals on 07818 581758.&lt;/p&gt;
